Brazilian Stock Movers: Hypermarcas, MRV Engenharia, Souza Cruz

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-05-09T14:24:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/brazilian-stock-movers-hypermarcas-mrv-engenharia-souza-cruz.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:03 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 0.1 percent to 64,332.32.  Hypermarcas SA (HYPE3)  (HYPE3 BS) plunged 8.7 percent to 18.49
reais. The consumer-goods company tumbled after it said that
first-quarter net income fell 40 percent from a year earlier to
32.9 million reais ($20.4 million). The average estimate of
eight analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was for net income
excluding some items of 129.3 million reais.  MRV Engenharia & Participacoes SA (MRVE3 BS) advanced 1.8
percent to 13.54 reais. It led gains by homebuilders as traders
pared bets for higher borrowing costs in  Brazil , boosting the
outlook for companies that depend on credit growth.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA (OGXP3 BS) rose 0.5
percent to 14.78 reais. The  oil company  controlled by
billionaire  Eike Batista  posted a first-quarter net loss of 33.9
million reais. A year earlier, the net loss was 56.9 million
reais, OGX said in a regulatory filing May 6.  Souza Cruz SA (CRUZ3)  (CRUZ3 BS) climbed 1.6 percent to 18.65
reais. Brazil’s biggest tobacco company reported first-quarter
net income of 415 million reais, a 24 percent increase from a
year earlier, according to a statement on the company’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
